41:32.506 --> 41:35.075
Why would you want to join
the US military?

41:35.542 --> 41:36.973
Because the military offers

41:36.975 --> 41:39.276
a tremendous amount
of opportunities for education.

41:39.278 --> 41:41.279
Last week you were joining ISIS,

41:41.281 --> 41:43.918
this week you joining
the US military?

41:45.852 --> 41:47.821
That...
that was an internet prank.

41:48.088 --> 41:50.624
A prank?
That's no prank young lady.

41:51.290 --> 41:52.758
I know it...

41:53.260 --> 41:55.995
- it was...
- It what, come on.

41:57.763 --> 41:58.932
It was just a game.

41:59.533 --> 42:00.601
A game?

42:01.533 --> 42:02.736
Bloody Warfare.

42:05.104 --> 42:07.675
It's a game my friends
and I used to play.

42:09.709 --> 42:11.044
A couple months ago...

42:12.745 --> 42:14.714
this player came on.

42:15.915 --> 42:18.651
And he just asked us
during the game...

42:19.318 --> 42:21.120
if we wanted to play
in real life.

42:21.988 --> 42:25.291
It's an online game
so you play with other people.

42:27.693 --> 42:28.761
Go on.

42:30.796 --> 42:32.263
He just asked us
during the game

42:32.265 --> 42:34.667
if we wanted
to play in real life...

42:35.334 --> 42:37.771
to become part of an army
in real life.

42:40.973 --> 42:43.008
He said if we flew to Syria...

42:44.010 --> 42:45.877
we could join the army
to help rescue

42:45.879 --> 42:47.014
women and children.

42:47.948 --> 42:50.117
We would fight
against the bad people there.

42:51.618 --> 42:53.153
He said we would do good.

42:55.354 --> 42:56.956
The player said he needed us.

42:57.323 --> 42:59.193
Gabby, who was this man?

43:00.292 --> 43:02.328
- I... I can't.
- Can't what?

43:04.698 --> 43:06.133
I can't say anything else.

43:17.977 --> 43:20.414
When we couldn't get overseas...

43:22.247 --> 43:23.751
he asked us if...

43:24.917 --> 43:26.086
if... if we...

43:28.254 --> 43:29.790
he sent us money.

43:32.859 --> 43:35.795
He wanted us to make bombs
to take to school but...

43:36.296 --> 43:38.332
that's when I said no,
I got out.

43:39.231 --> 43:40.666
He said he would kill us.

43:41.234 --> 43:44.037
Nobody's gonna hurt you,
doll face, nobody.

43:45.339 --> 43:47.340
Gabby, who was this man?

43:48.107 --> 43:50.207
I don't know,
he just messaged us

43:50.209 --> 43:51.743
through the game,
but I don't play anymore,

43:51.745 --> 43:52.813
I swear.

43:54.013 --> 43:55.415
Gabby, let's go for a walk.

44:01.053 --> 44:02.319
What?

44:02.321 --> 44:03.423
She's talking about bombing
a school.

44:03.656 --> 44:04.723
What is she, crazy?

44:04.925 --> 44:06.857
We need to call the FBI
and the police.

44:06.859 --> 44:08.392
Hold on, this is serious,

44:08.394 --> 44:10.396
we got to think about this,
this is bigger than Gabby.

44:15.401 --> 44:16.703
Hey, Mickey.

44:17.271 --> 44:19.039
Yeah, hello, doll face,
how are ya?

44:19.339 --> 44:22.138
- I'm good.
- You know, I never asked you,

44:22.140 --> 44:24.912
but I have an idea you work
for the government.

44:27.113 --> 44:28.248
What's going on?

44:53.173 --> 44:54.506
Did you get everything
loaded okay?

44:55.809 --> 44:59.812
One hundred 25-pound bags
of ammonium nitrate fertilizer.

45:00.080 --> 45:01.949
That will be 756 dollars.

45:28.107 --> 45:29.506
I've got friends telling me

45:29.508 --> 45:31.441
extremists are infiltrating
the armed forces.

45:31.443 --> 45:32.877
The government's
never gonna fall

45:32.879 --> 45:34.147
to political correctness.

45:34.347 --> 45:36.314
Seasoned guys are never gonna
allow what happened

45:36.316 --> 45:37.885
at Fort Hood to happen again.

45:38.385 --> 45:39.584
What else?

45:39.586 --> 45:40.821
You're right
about one thing, Soup.

45:44.890 --> 45:46.225
Um...

45:46.825 --> 45:51.062
Usually between Interpol,
CIA, NSA, FBI,

45:51.064 --> 45:54.165
we get about 200 to 300 hits
on terrorism

45:54.167 --> 45:55.969
- or extremist chatter a day.
- What kind of hits?

45:56.202 --> 45:58.571
An email,
intercepted phone call,

45:59.004 --> 46:01.307
um, maybe even
an encrypted recording.

46:01.540 --> 46:02.874
In the past few weeks,

46:02.876 --> 46:04.810
that number has risen
over a 1,000.

46:05.010 --> 46:06.213
Before 9/11,

46:06.446 --> 46:08.582
chatter concerning an attack
was all over the place.

46:09.216 --> 46:11.417
Thousands of pieces
of information.

46:12.084 --> 46:13.519
Everyone knew something
was gonna happen.

46:14.386 --> 46:16.356
That was the problem,
everyone knew something,

46:16.957 --> 46:19.326
but nobody worked collectively
to put it all together.

46:20.526 --> 46:23.428
My brother is with the FBI
in South Carolina.

46:23.430 --> 46:26.366
I called him just to check on
what he's been hearing.

46:26.966 --> 46:28.299
He began to tell me
about a group

46:28.301 --> 46:29.899
called the Underground Foocruft.

46:29.901 --> 46:31.003
I've heard of 'em.

46:33.339 --> 46:36.009
They've been around
for some 30 odd years.

46:36.343 --> 46:39.042
Small communities,
mostly in rural places,

46:39.044 --> 46:41.145
um, most Muslim.
They live together,

46:41.147 --> 46:43.247
they have their own sets
of laws.

46:43.249 --> 46:46.084
Years ago, they were connected
with acts of violence,

46:46.086 --> 46:48.285
assassinations,
stockpiling weapons.

46:48.287 --> 46:50.222
- How many are there?
- Twenty...

46:50.990 --> 46:53.560
maybe 30, scattered
across the United States.

46:54.394 --> 46:56.993
My brother said if there's an
infrastructure for terrorism

46:56.995 --> 46:59.932
in the United States,
this group already has it.

47:01.501 --> 47:02.602
That's a map
of where they're located.

47:04.169 --> 47:05.204
Brian.

47:06.372 --> 47:09.307
In every tactical operation,
there's a start point.

47:10.042 --> 47:12.375
How do they communicate
with each individual player

47:12.377 --> 47:13.479
to say, "Hey...

47:14.881 --> 47:16.283
attack, it's time".

47:17.182 --> 47:18.550
There has to be a trigger.

47:19.452 --> 47:21.921
We find the trigger,
we stop the attack.

47:24.124 --> 47:26.325
How do we find a trigger
that no one wants us to find?

47:27.060 --> 47:28.526
They would never trust
a strategy

47:28.528 --> 47:29.930
to just messages alone...

47:31.131 --> 47:32.531
it could get distorted.

47:39.138 --> 47:40.372
It's an event.

47:41.106 --> 47:43.275
It's an event that they control.

47:44.343 --> 47:46.512
And if we're not careful
with our investigation,

47:47.080 --> 47:48.248
we could speed it up.

47:49.048 --> 47:50.484
Okay guys, listen up.

47:51.218 --> 47:53.353
That was a buddy of mine,
police officer.

47:54.354 --> 47:56.053
He said a concerned citizen
called today

47:56.055 --> 47:58.959
to report a guy buying
2,500 pounds of fertilizer.

47:59.258 --> 48:00.558
- Ammonia nitrate?
- Yes.

48:00.560 --> 48:02.426
They have a person
and vehicle description,

48:02.428 --> 48:04.097
but haven't been able
to track him down.

48:07.367 --> 48:09.667
Hey guys, let's take
a break for dinner

48:09.669 --> 48:11.203
and meet back here in...

48:12.104 --> 48:13.205
uh, say, an hour?

48:14.307 --> 48:15.408
Okay, thanks.

48:16.176 --> 48:18.178
Thomas, hang on a minute.

48:24.350 --> 48:25.518
What's up, Soup?

48:26.385 --> 48:28.019
Brother, you guys are here
for training.

48:28.021 --> 48:29.022
No worries, we're good.

48:31.390 --> 48:33.693
Terrorist camps,
ammonium nitrate,

48:34.361 --> 48:36.263
questionable northern
border security.

48:38.196 --> 48:39.465
What I'm about to ask you...

48:41.401 --> 48:43.036
you got to be straight up
with me.

48:45.405 --> 48:48.006
We need guys monitoring
this Underground Foocruft.

48:48.640 --> 48:50.409
Luis Marcel at the resort,

48:51.077 --> 48:52.145
where he's going...

48:53.146 --> 48:55.414
I need your guy in Ohio
to get us more info.

48:57.149 --> 48:58.452
There's a pattern here.

48:59.352 --> 49:00.484
And we're not gonna solve it

49:00.486 --> 49:02.356
by sitting
in this conference room.

49:05.524 --> 49:08.595
What I'm asking you could cost
you your jobs...

49:10.396 --> 49:11.598
maybe more.

49:12.365 --> 49:16.502
But I can't sit by
and allow 9/11 to happen again.

49:18.305 --> 49:19.736
We've got to do something to...

49:19.738 --> 49:21.507
- Protect America.
- Exactly.

49:23.042 --> 49:24.676
- You gonna ask him?
- No need to,

49:25.077 --> 49:26.545
this is what we're trained
to do.

49:31.318 --> 49:33.453
- I'll let Erik know.
- Thanks, brother.

49:41.060 --> 49:44.063
- Carlene, I'm glad you...
- Soup, I'm gonna be blunt.

49:44.629 --> 49:47.032
Officially I'm required
to tell you to cease and desist.

49:47.232 --> 49:48.600
What, why?

49:48.602 --> 49:50.270
Because the threat
isn't considered credible.

49:51.470 --> 49:52.903
<i>It wasn't my call.</i>

49:52.905 --> 49:54.508
Personally, I think
you're on to something but,

49:54.774 --> 49:56.607
I'm glad at least someone
is remaining vigilant

49:56.609 --> 49:58.274
during an era
of political correctness

49:58.276 --> 50:00.213
and bruised egos.

50:02.048 --> 50:03.247
I have to run.

50:03.249 --> 50:05.216
But don't stop
what you're doing,

50:05.218 --> 50:06.386
and as a favor to me,

50:07.053 --> 50:07.754
be discreet.

50:08.354 --> 50:11.257
Oh, don't worry,
I'm always discreet.

50:21.533 --> 50:24.570
Erin, I'm gonna need you
to set up a deployment schedule.

50:25.305 --> 50:28.341
Alex, I need secure comps
for both teams.

50:28.707 --> 50:30.573
Have 'em go to dinner
and meet back in here

50:30.575 --> 50:32.109
for the warning order.

50:32.111 --> 50:33.743
Roy's deposited the funds
in the account

50:33.745 --> 50:35.145
for the operation.

50:35.147 --> 50:37.113
I want troops
in the field tonight.

50:37.115 --> 50:38.184
Yes, sir.

50:45.258 --> 50:47.326
Kamal, you're coming with me.

50:48.260 --> 50:50.128
- Where are we going?
- To a party.

50:50.763 --> 50:53.133
- Wear a suit.
- Seriously?

50:59.138 --> 51:01.207
- Are you Mr. Whit?
- I am.

51:01.607 --> 51:04.341
- Carlene sent me.
- You called Carlene?

51:04.343 --> 51:06.780
- What do you want from me?
- And you must be Gabby.

51:07.747 --> 51:09.281
Yes. Yes, sir.

51:10.383 --> 51:12.149
I'm gonna need to speak
with Gabby alone.

51:12.151 --> 51:14.484
No, the girl's gonna stay
with us.

51:14.486 --> 51:16.423
- Yeah.
- Okay.

51:18.191 --> 51:20.861
Gabby, I'm Wayne Schaffer,
I work with Mr. Whit's daughter.

51:22.127 --> 51:23.896
I need you to tell me everything

51:24.129 --> 51:25.495
that you discussed
with those gentlemen,

51:25.497 --> 51:26.732
and in great detail.

51:27.700 --> 51:29.434
And then I'm gonna ask you
to do something

51:29.734 --> 51:31.303
that's gonna take
a lot of courage.

51:31.504 --> 51:32.572
What?

51:33.705 --> 51:35.374
I need you to take
this flash drive

51:35.774 --> 51:38.577
and put it in the USB port
in all your friend's computers.

51:39.412 --> 51:40.881
But you got to do it
without them knowing.

51:42.182 --> 51:43.450
You gonna be able to do this?

51:44.716 --> 51:45.919
Yes.

51:46.519 --> 51:47.754
All right, good.

51:54.392 --> 51:55.896
Well let's take it
from the top here.

51:57.463 --> 51:58.531
I think it's...

51:59.397 --> 52:00.466
very awesome

52:00.700 --> 52:02.433
those guys would risk
their careers

52:02.435 --> 52:03.734
maybe even their lives

52:03.736 --> 52:06.239
to follow the threat
and try to stop it.

52:06.705 --> 52:07.807
It is.

52:09.207 --> 52:10.343
You would know.

52:11.877 --> 52:13.778
So are you gonna tell me
where we're going?

52:13.780 --> 52:15.582
So you gonna tell me
what's going on?

52:20.352 --> 52:22.556
The missing Al-Qaeda leaders
that disappeared...

52:24.222 --> 52:25.357
they didn't disappear.

52:26.225 --> 52:27.327
I know.

52:28.227 --> 52:29.662
I know they didn't disappear.

52:32.164 --> 52:33.532
They're not with other groups.

52:35.334 --> 52:37.267
They're being held
by United States.

52:37.269 --> 52:38.404
What?

52:38.703 --> 52:41.538
After Osama Bin Laden's death,
your CIA partnered

52:41.540 --> 52:43.741
with the Iraqi government
to secretly capture

52:43.743 --> 52:45.712
the last remaining commanders
of Al-Qaeda.

52:46.444 --> 52:47.546
It was a trick.

52:48.714 --> 52:51.883
The Iraqis promised
them protection, they didn't.

52:52.517 --> 52:54.320
They turned them over
to the CIA.

52:56.656 --> 52:58.792
- That makes no sense.
- Think about it.

53:00.225 --> 53:01.424
The Americans had just killed

53:01.426 --> 53:03.262
the most wanted man
in the world.

53:04.430 --> 53:07.765
His men needed protection.
One by one they came in secrecy

53:07.767 --> 53:11.203
and one by one they were
turned over to the Americans.

53:11.970 --> 53:13.439
- Gitmo?
- No.

53:14.473 --> 53:15.508
No.

53:15.742 --> 53:18.343
A separate prison inside
the United States.

53:18.778 --> 53:21.444
No way, they could never keep
that a secret.

53:21.446 --> 53:22.515
They did.

53:22.781 --> 53:24.283
How do you know this?

53:25.417 --> 53:27.486
One of the men,
Muhammad Jiran...

53:28.354 --> 53:29.489
is my brother.

53:29.955 --> 53:33.359
He was a double agent.
He was offered this deal.

53:34.593 --> 53:36.426
My father told him not to go,

53:36.428 --> 53:38.597
and like he feared,
Muhammad never came home.

53:40.499 --> 53:42.633
Iraqi regime, of course,
denies turning

53:42.635 --> 53:45.504
any of these men over
but it happened.

53:51.377 --> 53:53.678
How'd your brother get arrested
if he was a double agent?

53:54.513 --> 53:55.946
Because he's still
gathering intel

53:55.948 --> 53:57.650
from the prisoners
being brought in.

53:58.718 --> 54:00.886
These men talk in prison
and my brother listens.

54:04.289 --> 54:07.425
If you want to find out
anything global terrorism,

54:07.959 --> 54:12.363
The Perfect Day, trigger,
the infrastructure,

54:12.365 --> 54:15.334
strategy of an attack,
I need to talk to him.

54:20.339 --> 54:22.542
Kamal, I'm gonna need you
to stay in the truck.

54:24.977 --> 54:26.843
I got all dressed up
and rode here

54:26.845 --> 54:28.514
for you to leave me in the car?

54:30.615 --> 54:32.551
This isn't the right place
for you to be seen...

54:33.484 --> 54:34.620
at least not yet.

54:35.488 --> 54:37.557
Don't worry,
I'll bring you something.

55:16.528 --> 55:17.763
What are you doing here?

55:18.930 --> 55:21.400
What about this is discreet?

55:22.368 --> 55:23.536
Don't worry,

55:24.035 --> 55:25.137
you can trust me.

55:29.008 --> 55:31.511
So you, um, come alone?

55:33.078 --> 55:34.147
Kind of.

55:37.515 --> 55:38.885
- Hello.
- Hi.

55:39.084 --> 55:41.153
I'm sorry, son, I'm gonna have
to ask you to leave.

55:42.955 --> 55:45.790
No one invited you, Soup,
it was a gesture of good will.

55:46.091 --> 55:47.823
I didn't actually think
you would come.

55:47.825 --> 55:48.994
Yet, here I am.

55:50.129 --> 55:52.031
But you are late,
that's strike one.

55:54.466 --> 55:56.102
- Ladies.
- Thank you.

55:56.669 --> 55:58.737
- You should try one.
- I'm good.

55:59.370 --> 56:02.541
My wife made those personally,
lieutenant.

56:02.774 --> 56:05.577
- That's strike two.
- Sir, can I have a moment?

56:07.713 --> 56:08.714
Sure.

56:15.120 --> 56:16.756
What do you know
about The Perfect Day?

56:19.591 --> 56:21.491
What do you know
about the secret prison

56:21.493 --> 56:23.830
that's holding top level
Al-Qaeda operatives...

56:24.629 --> 56:26.098
right here in the United States?

56:28.600 --> 56:29.767
And that's strike three.

56:30.502 --> 56:31.838
Good to see you again, Campbell.

56:51.022 --> 56:52.524
Went that well, yeah?

56:58.196 --> 56:59.631
Do you trust me, Kamal?

57:00.798 --> 57:02.634
You're the only one I do trust.

58:25.917 --> 58:27.252
Everyone's in the field, sir.

58:31.156 --> 58:33.326
- Expecting someone?
- Yup.

58:34.827 --> 58:35.995
Any minute now.

58:48.073 --> 58:49.576
I need to talk to you.

58:56.582 --> 58:57.783
Last night,

58:57.982 --> 58:59.718
what were you talking about
with the admiral?

59:01.821 --> 59:03.056
Have you lost your mind?

59:03.722 --> 59:04.856
What are you doing?

59:06.825 --> 59:08.292
You have a known
international terrorist

59:08.294 --> 59:10.227
saying things like
The Perfect Day

59:10.229 --> 59:12.832
on a phone call traced back
to Heathrow Airport.

59:13.265 --> 59:14.765
You have increased
chatter of threats.

59:15.566 --> 59:18.870
You have a secret prison
harboring terrorists illegally.

59:19.305 --> 59:20.738
You have a suspected terrorist

59:20.740 --> 59:22.774
making multiple trips
into the US

59:23.042 --> 59:24.877
under the radar through Canada

59:25.176 --> 59:26.745
carrying large amounts of cash.

59:27.044 --> 59:29.648
Small operatives are preparing
for something big.

59:30.249 --> 59:33.917
Just yesterday, an Arabic man
was spotted in eastern Ohio

59:33.919 --> 59:37.390
buying 2,500 pounds
of ammonium nitrate.

59:39.892 --> 59:41.758
We're running
our own investigation.

59:41.760 --> 59:42.994
Listen Paul,

59:43.328 --> 59:45.131
if they find out
we're on to them,

59:45.865 --> 59:46.966
it's over.

59:47.732 --> 59:48.868
You have any men on this?

59:49.334 --> 59:52.070
- Possibly.
- Who, where?

59:52.870 --> 59:53.872
I can't tell you that.

59:55.307 --> 59:57.377
Something's going to happen

59:57.776 --> 01:00:00.111
